            "brief_summary": "The optimal management of mineral and bone disorders associated to chronic kidney disease (CKD-MBD) is a daily challenge for nephrologists. Its consequences may be immediate (biological abnormalities such as hypocalcemia, hyperphosphatemia, hyperparathyroidism, etc.) or delayed (fractures, renal osteodystrophy, vascular calcifications, increased morbi-mortality and growth retardation in the youngest patients). CKD-MBD is defined by the association of one or more of the following abnormalities: 1",
